C++ class 'CCmdLine' parses application command line arguments.

This class was written by Chris Losinger, Smaller Animals Software.
http://www.smalleranimals.com

The source code was primary written for use with Windows and MFC.
Minor adjustments to the code have been done to make it run on Linux.
All changes to the code have been marked with the comment "EMWHBR".

Files:
------
cmd_line.h		Implements the
cmd_line.cpp		C++ class 'CCmdLine'

test_cmd_line.cpp	Test application

Makefile		Makefile for this project

README			This file

Example output from test application:
-------------------------------------

> test_cmd_line_dbg.x86_64
------------- COMMAND LINE ARGUMENTS ------------

g_remote_ip_addr : 192.168.100.17
g_remote_port    : 24000
g_local_port     : 14000
g_delay          : 0.1
g_verbose        : 0

-------------------------------------------------

> test_cmd_line_dbg.x86_64 -delay 12.34 -v -tcp 4.5.6.7 88 99
------------- COMMAND LINE ARGUMENTS ------------

g_remote_ip_addr : 4.5.6.7
g_remote_port    : 88
g_local_port     : 99
g_delay          : 12.34
g_verbose        : 1

-------------------------------------------------
